# Reaction → action mappings (consumer-side). Copy to reactions.tsv and edit.
# Format: <emoji>\t<action>   (tab-separated, one per line; # lines are comments)
# A self-placed reaction with a matching row runs its action; the action is a
# natural-language instruction the handler carries out. {permalink} is replaced
# with the reacted message's permalink from the event body.
# Examples:
# :ticket:	create a ticket from the message: run `<your ticket command> {permalink}`
# :eyes:	start tracking this thread
